{
  "message": "fuzz(ext4-htree-mmp): 23 structured seeds covering both parsers\n\nExisting 7 seeds left both parser branches sparsely covered. Add 23\nseeds that pin the harness's two parsers across their meaningful\nphase space:\n\n  parse_dx_root / parse_dx_root_with_large_dir:\n    * indirect_levels = 0/1/2 (normal-mode boundary)\n    * indirect_levels = 3 (LARGEDIR-only \u2014 exposes mode divergence)\n    * indirect_levels = 4 (rejected by both)\n    * reserved_zero != 0, info_length != 8, unused_flags != 0\n    * count = 0 / count > limit / max-density 8-entry block\n    * hash_version = legacy/TEA/SIPHASH (each branch enumerated)\n\n  Ext4MmpBlock::parse_from_bytes:\n    * seq = 1, MAX, CLEAN, FSCK, MAX+1 (UnsafeUnknown sentinel)\n    * wrong magic (early reject)\n    * 64-byte non-NUL-terminated nodename (full-capacity boundary)\n    * check_interval = u16::MAX\n    * nonzero checksum field\n\n2.3M runs / 13s post-seed surface no crashes.",
